'''Eternal Decision''' is an [[United States|American]] [[Christian metal]] band.  Musically the band blends [[Pantera]] influenced riffs, with a mix of [[James Hetfield]]/[[Phil Anselmo]] styled vocals. In 1997 the band released their critically acclaimed  self titled debut throughout the United States  and 16 other different countries.<ref>http://www.allmusic.com/cg/amg.dll?p=amg&sql=11:5q63trprkl5x</ref> They have since gone on to release 2 more full length studio albums, 1999's "Ghost in the Machine" and 2002's "E.D. III".<ref>http://www.heavensmetal.com/cgi-bin/band.cgi?BandNum=20081</ref> Their second album "Ghost in the Machine" had 2 songs chart in the top 5 on the Pure Rock Report.<ref>https://www.cdbaby.com/cd/eternald3</ref>

==Current Members==
*Joe Chambless - Bass and Vocals
*Cory Boatright - Guitar and Vocals 
*Tommy Torres - Guitar 
*Kirk Campbell - Drums 
==Former Members==
*Dave Perkins - Vocals

==Discography==
*''Eternal Decision'' (1997 Cling, Godfather)
*''Ghost in the Machine'' (1999 Godfather)
*''E.D. III'' (2002 Godfather)

==Trivia==
*Mainly due to the similarities in vocal style, the group is often mistaken for [[Metallica]]. The song ''Hunger'' from the self titled debut recieved many downloads on [[Napster]] due to the fact that many people falsely believed it to be a new Metallica song. <ref>http://artfortheears.freeservers.com/index2/interviews/edecision/edecision.htm</ref>

